main event: An observer reported seeing a round amber object in Columbia, MO, which was determined to be a parachute jumper.
interesting points: The object was described as round and amber, too slow to be a satellite; it had no discernible features or rapid movements,The observer used 50 power binoculars for the sighting,The sighting lasted for approximately 30 minutes, The observer had extensive aviation experience, including being a licensed radio engineer and a retired Air Force captain,The weather was cold and overcast at the time of the sighting.
witness description: Civilian with extensive aviation and radio engineering experience.
